summary_text: 1. I was in the boy scouts. 2. We were doing the 50-yard dash. 3. The race was at the pier. 4. There were about eight or nine of us racing. 5. I caught cramps on the third round. 6. I started yelling for help. 7. The fellows didn't believe me. 8. They thought I was slowing down to catch up. 9. Everyone else kept going. 10. The scoutmaster was watching me. 11. He didn't pay me any attention. 12. A guy who just walked up jumped in to grab me.
